                        Ball at Hawking's 

00:00:33.281 --> 00:00:35.764
is a unique spectacle 

00:00:35.764 --> 00:00:39.156
because the actors taking part in 

00:00:39.156 --> 00:00:41.925
it are both healthy individuals and people with disabilities.

00:00:41.925 --> 00:00:46.836
They are all professional actors - graduates of 
 higher schools of theater and acting workshops.

00:00:46.487 --> 00:00:50.114
The uniqueness of this show is also 

00:00:50.114 --> 00:00:54.447
in the fact that it talks about Stephen Hawking,

00:00:54.447 --> 00:01:00.576
who himself is an extraordinary person - a brilliant astrophysicist,

00:01:00.576 --> 00:01:02.576
struggling with an incurable disease.

00:01:09.106 --> 00:01:12.382
When he was 21 years old and he was still a student,

00:01:12.382 --> 00:01:18.803
he learned that he suffered from amyotrophic lateral sclerosis,

00:01:18.803 --> 00:01:21.803
, and doctors predicted his life as no more than two years of age.

00:01:24.969 --> 00:01:27.728
"You are so very dependent on others,

00:01:27.728 --> 00:01:30.646
you can not  eat ,

00:01:30.646 --> 00:01:35.646
you can not pee , you can not stand, sit, lie down ...

00:01:36.416 --> 00:01:40.540
Stephen Hawking celebrated in January 2012 his 70th birthday,

00:01:40.542 --> 00:01:46.490
so his incurable illness lasts from a half-century. 

00:01:46.494 --> 00:01:50.490
So, he has overcome it ....
You can tell that it is a miracle 

00:01:50.487 --> 00:01:54.230
and he is a real miracle:

00:01:54.227 --> 00:01:59.260
it shows us that you can do everything

00:01:59.256 --> 00:02:03.740
if you have the strength, faith and spiritual possibilities.

00:02:04.041 --> 00:02:07.600
"I feel myself an approaching life - when 
 everything I want is to die. 

00:02:07.601 --> 00:02:10.210
Quiet, quiet, quiet, quiet... Death!

00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:16.000
Silence!

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:23.000
Truce, silence, dream. "

